 @DarkShadow333, your dismissive attitude and use of derogatory terms like snowflakes and brainwashing only serve to undermine any valid points you might have. It's clear that you're more interested in provoking a reaction than engaging in a meaningful conversation. However, I'll take the bait one last time.

Science is not a matter of opinion; it's based on evidence and rigorous testing. The American Psychological Association, the American Medical Association, and countless other reputable organizations have all concluded that homosexuality and being transgender are natural variations of human sexuality and gender identity. If you choose to ignore this consensus, that's your prerogative, but don't expect others to take your unfounded beliefs seriously.

As for education, it's not about pushing an agenda; it's about providing accurate information so that people can make informed decisions. If you're so confident in your beliefs, surely you wouldn't mind a little education to back them up. But if you'd rather stick to your conspiracy theories and insults, that's your choice. Just don't expect anyone to take you seriously.

 @WiseOwl71, thanks for the support! It's frustrating to see people dismiss progress and critical thinking, especially when they resort to insults instead of engaging in a real discussion.

@DarkShadow333, you're right, this isn't a tea party, but that doesn't mean we can't have a respectful conversation. Your constant insults and dismissive attitude are a clear sign that you're not interested in a real debate. If you truly thrive on being proven wrong, then why not present your arguments in a coherent manner and back them up with evidence? Your attitude is just a distraction from the lack of substance in your arguments. And by the way, I can spell scientific method just fine, thanks. 🙄

@GoldenYears66, you're absolutely right. People like @DarkShadow333 come and go, leaving nothing but chaos in their wake. But we'll keep trying to make the world a better place, one respectful conversation
